msContents.summary: Complete, illustrated copy of the Shāhnāmah with 4 miniatures; textblock is written on darker paper that has been reset into lighter frames; catchwords have been trimmed around, but not pasted down; some section headings are missing.

author.name: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: xi, 499, xi leaves : 307 x 250 (200 x 120) mm bound to 317 x 235 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: 25 lines in four columns; border-ruled and columns ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece in blue, red and gold (f. 1v, 267v) with illuminated floral marginal fill in gold, blue and red around the page-opening (f. 1v-2r, 267v-268r). A similar floral marginal fill is on each page-opening holding an illustration (f. 6v-7r, 48v-49r, 54v-55r, 57v-58r). Four illustrations with a full page miniature in polychrome and gold on one side (f. 6v, 48v, 55r, 58r) and on the reverse a large drawing of a flowering plant in gold with blue, red and green accents (f. 6r, 48r, 55v, 58v). A floral finispiece in gold, green and red (f. 266r)

binding.p: Bound in modern cloth half binding; dark blue spine and corners, light blue sides; stamped on spine "Shāh-nāmah Firdausi Persian Manuscript 14th century" with gold tooling along the ribs and gold stamped vignettes between them.

origin.p: The colophon is missing; the leaves were probably reset and the illustrations added in the late 17th or early 18th century.

history.provenance: Sold at Sotheby's in November 1922, lot 230 (catalog entry with date written in pencil pasted in f. 499v).
Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.

keywords.term: Illumination of books and manuscripts, Iranian--Specimens
